(8067, 677, 'historical_content', '<strong>Qingdao is a major seaport, naval base and vital economic center in China. It is rich in history and vibrant with global tourism.</strong>\r\n\r\nIn recent years, Qingdao’s development has been sparked by the government’s establishment of the Blue Economic Zone – designed to attract the high-tech industry. The zone focuses on developing modern infrastructure to support advanced manufacturing, including cutting-edge goods production to strengthen Qingdao’s position as a key regional economic center. Today, focus is also given to cultural and entertainment growth in Qingdao and Huangdao.'),
