(1155, 1, '2016-07-08 10:27:46', '2016-07-08 10:27:46', '<h3>Jack Gao, Vice President of Wanda Cultural Industry Group, and Adam Aron, AMC Chief Executive Officer and President, take a photo together.</h3>\r\nAMC Theatres, owned by Wanda Group, signed a definitive merger agreement with Carmike Cinemas, Inc. on March 3, 2016. Under the terms of the agreement, AMC will acquire Carmike for $1.1 billion. Together AMC and Carmike own 663 theatre locations and 8,380 screens in 45 states across the United States, and the merger will solidify their position as the largest movie theatre chain in the world.\r\n\r\nThis transaction will also make Wanda Group the number one movie theatre operator in both China and the US, increasing Wanda’s market share in the global film industry and expanding their influence in Hollywood.\r\n\r\nAMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. was listed on the New York Stock Exchange in 2013. The acquisition of Carmike was completed independently by AMC, leveraging the US capital markets without any funding from Wanda Group. Wanda Group has increased their market share by listing acquired companies for further acquisitions in the global cinema industry. Previously, Wanda Cinema Line in China also acquired Australian cinema chain Hoyts Cinema, a purchase that underscores the company’s ambition to build the world’s largest and most widely distributed cinema line network.\r\n\r\nAMC was originally the second largest cinema chain in the US, owning 5,426 screens that are predominantly located in the downtown areas of major cities in the country. It operates the most productive theatres in the top US markets, and boasts the greatest market share in the three largest markets (New York, Los Angeles and Chicago).\r\n\r\nA NASDAQ-listed company, Carmike Cinemas is the fourth largest cinema operator in the US with 276 cinemas and 2,954 screens, the majority of which are located in suburban and rural areas. With this acquisition, AMC will surpass US-based Regal Entertainment as the world’s largest cinema operator.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'AMC Theatres to acquire Carmike Cinemas, creating largest chain of movie theatres in the world', 'AMC Theatres, owned by Wanda Group, signed a definitive merger agreement with Carmike Cinemas, Inc. on March 3, 2016. Under the terms of...', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1129-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 10:27:46', '2016-07-08 10:27:46', '', 1129, 'http://ready-for-feedback2.com/flowasia/wanda/1129-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1156, 1, '2016-07-08 10:28:03', '2016-07-08 10:28:03', 'Wanda Group Chairman Wang Jianlin entered the list of Fortune China''s 50 Most Influential Business Leaders in China which was issued on April 14.\r\n\r\nThose joining Mr. Wang on the list are all business leaders with cross-industry visions and concepts. They have always been making effort to search for new tools, channels and management methods to improve efficiency and customer experiences.\r\n\r\nWhen referring to Dalian Wanda Group, Fortune China commented: Amid lackluster global and domestic growth, Dalian Wanda Group realized RMB 290.16 billion in revenue in 2015, up 19.1% YoY. Its profit was also estimated to increase significantly over the previous year. In 2015, revenue from services represents 43% of the group''s total revenue, up 10 percentage points compared with 2014. Rental income from commercial properties increased over 30%. The group''s asset-light strategy has been expanding successfully.\r\n\r\nThe Wanda Cultural Industry Group, a subsidiary founded merely three years ago, has been growing its revenue by tens of billions yuan every year. The Wanda Cinema Line went public on Jan 2015, becoming the first listed cinema operator in China. Its stock price surged 102% as of the end of 2015, making it a cinema operator with the largest market cap globally. It also became a component of the CSI 300. As of Dec 30, 2015, Dalian Wanda Group''s total overseas investments exceeded USD 15 billion, and Mr. Wang is still expanding his territories abroad in 2016.', 'Wang Jianlin on Fortune China''s list of China''s Most Influential Business Leaders', 'Wanda Group Chairman Wang Jianlin entered the list of Fortune China''s 50 Most Influential Business Leaders in China which was issued on April 14.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1132-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 10:28:03', '2016-07-08 10:28:03', '', 1132, 'http://ready-for-feedback2.com/flowasia/wanda/1132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1157, 1, '2016-07-08 10:28:41', '2016-07-08 10:28:41', 'TIME named Dalian Wanda Group Chairman Wang Jianlin to the 2016 TIME 100, its annual list of the 100 most influential people in the world.\r\n\r\nThe TIME 100 fall into five categories - Titans, Pioneers, Artists, Leaders and Icons. Mr. Wang Jianlin is named under Titans.\r\n\r\nOther Titans honorees include Apple CEO Tim Cook, Facebook founder Mark Zukerberg and his wife Priscilla Chan.', 'Wang Jianlin named to the 2016 TIME 100 List of the Most Influential People in the World', 'TIME named Dalian Wanda Group Chairman Wang Jianlin to the 2016 TIME 100, its annual list of the 100 most influential people in the world.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1138-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 10:28:41', '2016-07-08 10:28:41', '', 1138, 'http://ready-for-feedback2.com/flowasia/wanda/1138-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1158, 1, '2016-07-08 10:29:02', '2016-07-08 10:29:02', '<h3>Chicago Mayor Emanuel made the announcement of project land settlement</h3>\r\nThe Wanda Chicago Project successfully completed land settlement after the Chicago City Council unanimously approved its development plan. Chicago Mayor Rahm Emanuel congratulated the Chicago Project Company and project partner Magellan Development Group on the project site.\r\n\r\nMayor Emanuel made the announcement of project land settlement on site to over ten local media. When answering media questions, Mayor Emanuel once again expressed gratitude to Wanda Group for choosing Chicago as the first city for project development investment in US.\r\n\r\nThe Chicago Project, a mixture of condominiums and a Wanda Vista Hotel, is 361.5 meters high, and will be the third tallest building in Chicago upon completion.', 'Wanda Chicago project completes land settlement, marking the City’s 3rd tallest building', 'The Wanda Chicago Project successfully completed land settlement after the Chicago City Council unanimously approved its development plan...', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1141-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-08 10:29:02', '2016-07-08 10:29:02', '', 1141, 'http://ready-for-feedback2.com/flowasia/wanda/1141-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
